  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": true,
    "source": "whisper_local",
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "In programming, when things get too complex, we break it down."
      },
      {
        "start": 4.0,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "We've seen this with functions and with data structures."
      },
      {
        "start": 7.4,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "But how do we break down an object?"
      },
      {
        "start": 11.5,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "Well, we just take that one object and turn it into several smaller objects."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.7,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "That each focus on one specific job."
      },
      {
        "start": 20.2,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "We call this concept object composition, where one object has another object."
      },
      {
        "start": 27.2,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "This is just another way of organizing our code."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.1,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "We're nesting an object inside of another object."
      },
      {
        "start": 35.8,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "To access the attributes and methods on that nested object,"
      },
      {
        "start": 40.1,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "we just need to take it layer by layer."
      },
      {
        "start": 44.2,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "So let's say we have a playlist class and a song class,"
      },
      {
        "start": 48.2,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "where a playlist has a list of song objects."
      },
      {
        "start": 52.3,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "That it stores in the attribute Q."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.0,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "A song has a title and artist attribute and a method play."
      },
      {
        "start": 62.3,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "So if I have a playlist object K-pop, how do I access the title of the next song?"
      },
      {
        "start": 69.7,
        "duration": 5.7,
        "text": "First layer, we access the Q attribute of our playlist object using .sintx."
      },
      {
        "start": 76.6,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "That gives us a list of songs."
      },
      {
        "start": 80.0,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Then we index into that list to get the next song."
      },
      {
        "start": 84.2,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "Which gives us a song object."
      },
      {
        "start": 87.7,
        "duration": 5.9,
        "text": "Then to access the title attribute of that song object, we use .sintx again."
      },
      {
        "start": 95.4,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "And the fun part, if we want, we can combine all of the steps into a single line."
      },
      {
        "start": 101.6,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "If we want to play the next song, we follow the same access pattern."
      },
      {
        "start": 106.3,
        "duration": 5.6,
        "text": "But at the end, instead of accessing the song's title attribute, we call its play method."
      },
      {
        "start": 113.7,
        "duration": 7.6,
        "text": "This gives us a nice separation of concerns, where the playlist class is just responsible for managing songs."
      },
      {
        "start": 122.1,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "Or as the song class is where all of the logic lives for playing an actual audio track."
      },
      {
        "start": 129.6,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "Okay, but really, why is this better than just putting all the logic into a single class?"
      },
      {
        "start": 135.6,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "Say we're building a mining game, where a character can use different tools to break blocks of the terrain."
      },
      {
        "start": 141.8,
        "duration": 6.8,
        "text": "The effectiveness of that mining action combines the character's strength with the tools power."
      },
      {
        "start": 148.6,
        "duration": 7.5,
        "text": "After each mining action, the character's stamina decreases, and the tools durability decreases,"
      },
      {
        "start": 156.2,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "until it eventually breaks when it reaches zero."
      },
      {
        "start": 159.3,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "So, if I write that class real quick, we have all of these attributes, and a mine method."
      },
      {
        "start": 166.2,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "Now, what are the weaknesses of this approach?"
      },
      {
        "start": 170.1,
        "duration": 7.5,
        "text": "For one, it's kind of confusing, because this one class is really modeling two concepts,"
      },
      {
        "start": 177.6,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "a person and a tool."
